obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (26808)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. The proviso omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26808&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Protection of Human`
  line `Rights Act, 1993.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 28th day of September, 1993.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (26809)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26809&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "armed forces" means the naval, military and air forces and includes any other armed forces`
  line `of the Union;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Commission or of the State Commission, as the`
  line `case may be;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) "Chief Commissioner" means the Chief Commissioner for Persons with Disabilities`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 74 of the Rights of Persons with Disabilities Act, 2016 (49 of`
  line `2016);]`
  line
  line `(c) "Commission" means the National Human Rights Commission constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "Human Rights" means the rights relating to life, liberty, equality and dignity of the`
  line `individual guaranteed by the Constitution or embodied in the International Covenants and`
  line `enforceable by courts in India;`
  line
  line `(e) "Human Rights Court" means the Human Rights Court specified under section 30;`
  line
  line `^2[(f) "International Covenants" means the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights`
  line `and the International Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights adopted by the General`
  line `Assembly of the United Nations on the 16th December, 1966 and such other Covenant or Convention`
  line `adopted by the General Assembly of the United Nations as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify;]`
  line
  line `^3[(g) "Member" means a Member of the Commission or of the State Commission, as the case`
  line `may be;]`
  line
  line `^4[(ga) "National Commission for Backward Classes" means the National Commission for`
  line `Backward Classes constituted under section 3 of the National Commission for Backward Classes Act,`
  line `1993 (27 of 1993);]`
  line
  line `(h) "National Commission for Minorities" means the National Commission for Minorities`
  line `constituted under section 3 of the National Commission for Minorities Act, 1992 (19 of 1992);`
  line
  line `^5[(ha) "National Commission for Protection of Child Rights" means the National Commission for`
  line `Protection of Child Rights constituted under section 3 of the Commissions for Protection of Child`
  line `Rights Act, 2005 (4 of 2006);]`
  line
  line `^6[(i) "National Commission for the Scheduled Castes" means the National Commission for the`
  line `Scheduled Castes referred to in article 338 of the Constitution;]`
  line
  line `(ia) "National Commission for the Scheduled Tribes" means the National Commission for the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes referred to in article 338A of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(j) "National Commission for Women" means the National Commission for Women constituted`
  line `under section 3 of the National Commission for Women Act, 1990 (20 of 1990);`
  line
  line `(k) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(l) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "public servant" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 21 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(n) "State Commission" means a State Human Rights Commission constituted under section 21.`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to a law, which is not in force in the State of Jammu and Kashmir,`
  line `shall, in relation to that State, be construed as a reference to a corresponding law, if any, in force in that`
  line State.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Ladakh (UT).--`
  line
  line `Section 2.---Omit sub-section (2).`
  line `[Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 2, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (g) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (i) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (26810)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of a National Human Rights Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26810&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `constitute a body to be known as the National Human Rights Commission to exercise the powers`
  line `conferred upon, and to perform the functions assigned to, it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson who has been a ^1[Chief Justice of India or a Judge] of the Supreme Court;`
  line
  line `(b) one Member who is, or has been, a Judge of the Supreme Court;`
  line
  line `(c) one Member who is, or has been, the Chief Justice of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(d) ^2[three Members out of which at least one shall be a woman] to be appointed from amongst`
  line `persons having knowledge of, or practical experience in, matters relating to human rights`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairpersons of ^3[,the National Commission for Backward Classes, the National Commission`
  line `for Minorities, the National Commission for Protection of Child Rights],`
  line `^4[the National Commission for`
  line `the Scheduled Castes, the National Commission for the Scheduled Tribes] and the ^5[the National`
  line `Commission for Women and the Chief Commissioner for Persons with Disabilities] shall be deemed to be`
  line `Members of the Commission for the discharge of functions specified in clauses (b) to (j) of section 12.`
  line
  line `(4) There shall be a Secretary-General who shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the Commission`
  line `and ^6[shall, subject to control of the Chairperson, exercise all administrative and financial powers (except`
  line `judicial functions and the power to make regulations under section 40B)].`
  line
  line `(5) The headquarters of the Commission shall be at Delhi and the Commission may, with the`
  line `previous approval of the Central Government, establish offices at other places in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 3, for “Chief Justice” (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “two Members” (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “National Commission for Minorities” (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 3, for “the National Commission for the Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes”`
  line `(w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 3, for “National Commission for Women” (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 3, for certain words (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (26811)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Chairperson and other Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26811&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and ^1[the Members]`
  line `shall be appointed by the President by warrant under his hand and seal:`
  line
  line `Provided that every appointment under this sub-section shall be made after obtaining the`
  line `recommendations of a Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Prime Minister ---chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Speaker of the House of the People ---member;`
  line
  line `(c) Minister in-charge of the Ministry of Home`
  line `Affairs in the Government of India`
  line ----member;
  line
  line `(d) Leader of the Opposition in the House of`
  line `the People`
  line ---member;
  line
  line `(e) Leader of the Opposition in the Council of`
  line States
  line ---member;
  line
  line `(f) Deputy Chairman of the Council of States ---member:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no sitting Judge of the Supreme Court or sitting Chief Justice of a High Court`
  line `shall be appointed except after consultation with the Chief Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(2) No appointment of a Chairperson or a Member shall be invalid merely by reason of any`
  line `^2[vacancy of any member in the Committee referred to in the first proviso to sub-section (1)].`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "other Members" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 4, for "vacancy in the Committee" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006)`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (26812)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Resignation and removal of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for section 5 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26812&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[5. Resignation and removal of Chairperson and Members.—(1) The Chairperson or any`
  line `Member may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the President of India, resign his office.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), the Chairperson or any Member shall only be`
  line `removed from his office by order of the President of India on the ground of proved misbehaviour or`
  line `incapacity after the Supreme Court, on reference being made to it by the President, has, on inquiry held in`
  line `accordance with the procedure prescribed in that behalf by the Supreme Court, reported that the`
  line `Chairperson or the Member, as the case may be, ought on any such ground to be removed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (2), the President may, by order, remove from office the`
  line `Chairperson or any Member if the Chairperson or such Member, as the case may be,—`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his`
  line `office; or`
  line
  line `(c) is unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of mind or body; or`
  line
  line `(d) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(e) is convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which in the opinion of the`
  line `President involves moral turpitude.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (26813)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26813&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Term of office of Chairperson and Members.--(1) A person appointed as Chairperson shall`
  line `hold office for a term of ^2[three years] from the date on which he enters upon his office or until he attains`
  line `the age of seventy years, whichever is earlier ^3[and shall be eligible for re-appointment].`
  line
  line `(2) A person appointed as a Member shall hold office for a term of ^2[three years] from the date on`
  line `which he enters upon his office and shall be eligible for re-appointment ^4***:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Member shall hold office after he has attained the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(3) On ceasing to hold office, a Chairperson or a Member shall be ineligible for further employment`
  line `under the Government of India or under the Government of any State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006 s. 6, for section 6 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 4, for “five years” (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 4, ibid.(w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The words “for another term of five years” omitted by Act 19 of 2019, s. 4 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (26814)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Member to act as Chairperson or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26814&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) In`
  line `the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or otherwise, the President may, by notification, authorise one of the Members to act as the`
  line `Chairperson until the appointment of a new Chairperson to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairperson is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence on leave or`
  line `otherwise, such one of the Members as the President may, by notification, authorise in this behalf, shall`
  line `discharge the functions of the Chairperson until the date on which the Chairperson resumes his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (26815)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 7, for section (8) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26815&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[8. Terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.—The salaries and allowances`
  line `payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and Members shall be such`
  line `as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member shall be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (26816)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate the proceedings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26816&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `No act or`
  line `proceedings of the Commission shall be questioned or shall be invalidated merely on the ground of`
  line `existence of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (26817)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Procedure to be regulated by the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26817&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall meet at such`
  line `time and place as the Chairperson may think fit.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the Commission shall have`
  line `the power to lay down by regulations its own procedure.]`
  line
  line `(3) All orders and decisions of the Commission shall be authenticated by the`
  line `Secretary-General or any other officer of the Commission duly authorised by the Chairperson in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (26818)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Officers and other staff of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26818&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall make`
  line `available to the Commission—`
  line
  line `(a) an officer of the rank of the Secretary to the Government of India who shall be the`
  line `Secretary-General of the Commission; and`
  line
  line `(b) such police and investigative staff under an officer not below the rank of a Director`
  line `General of Police and such other officers and staff as may be necessary for the efficient`
  line `performance of the functions of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in this behalf, the`
  line `Commission may appoint such other administrative, technical and scientific staff as it may consider`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(3) The salaries, allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other staff appointed`
  line `under sub-section (2) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (26819)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Functions of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26819&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall perform all or any of the following`
  line `functions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) inquire, suo motu or on a petition presented to it by a victim or any person on his behalf ^1`
  line [or
  line `on a direction or order of any court], into complaint of—`
  line
  line `(i) violation of human rights or abetment thereof; or`
  line
  line `(ii) negligence in the prevention of such violation, by a public servant;`
  line
  line `(b) intervene in any proceeding involving any allegation of violation of human rights pending`
  line `before a court with the approval of such court;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(c) visit, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, any`
  line `jail or other institution under the control of the State Government, where persons are detained or`
  line `lodged for purposes of treatment, reformation or protection, for the study of the living conditions of`
  line `the inmates thereof and make recommendations thereon to the Government;]`
  line
  line `(d) review the safeguards provided by or under the Constitution or any law for the time`
  line `being in force for the protection of human rights and recommend measures for their effective`
  line implementation;
  line
  line `(e) review the factors, including acts of terrorism, that inhibit the enjoyment of human rights`
  line `and recommend appropriate remedial measures;`
  line
  line `(f) study treaties and other international instruments on human rights and make`
  line `recommendations for their effective implementation;`
  line
  line `(g) undertake and promote research in the field of human rights;`
  line
  line `(h) spread human rights literacy among various sections of society and promote awareness of the`
  line `safeguards available for the protection of these rights through publications, the media, seminars`
  line `and other available means;`
  line
  line `(i) encourage the efforts of non-governmental organisations and institutions working in the field`
  line `of human rights;`
  line
  line `(j) such other functions as it may consider necessary for the promotion of human rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006)`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (26820)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Powers relating to inquiries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 2006, s.10 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26820&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall, while inquiring into complaints`
  line `under this Act, have all the powers of a civil court trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908), and in particular in respect of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses and examining them on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall have power to require any person, subject to any privilege which may be`
  line `claimed by that person under any law for the time being in force, to furnish information on such points or`
  line `matters as, in the opinion of the Commission, may be useful for, or relevant to, the subject matter of the`
  line `inquiry and any person so required shall be deemed to be legally bound to furnish such`
  line `information within the meaning of section 176 and section 177 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission or any other officer, not below the rank of a Gazetted Officer, specially`
  line `authorised in this behalf by the Commission may enter any building or place where the Commission`
  line `has reason to believe that any document relating to the subject matter of the inquiry may be found, and`
  line `may seize any such document or take extracts or copies therefrom subject to the provisions of section`
  line `100 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), in so far as it may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court and when any offence as is described in`
  line `section 175, section 178, section 179, section 180 or section 228 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) is committed in the view or presence of the Commission, the Commission may, after`
  line `recording the facts constituting the offence and the statement of the accused as provided for in the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), forward the case to a Magistrate having jurisdiction to`
  line `try the same and the Magistrate to whom any such case is forwarded shall proceed to hear the complaint`
  line `against the accused as if the case has been forwarded to him under section 346 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973.`
  line
  line `(5) Every proceeding before the Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860), and the Commission shall be deemed to be a civil court for all the purposes of section 195`
  line `and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(6) Where the Commission considers it necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by order, transfer`
  line `any complaint filed or pending before it to the State Commission of the State from which the complaint`
  line `arises, for disposal in accordance with the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such complaint shall be transferred unless the same is one respecting which the State`
  line `Commission has jurisdiction to entertain the same.`
  line
  line `(7) Every complaint transferred under sub-section (6) shall be dealt with and disposed of by the State`
  line `Commission as if it were a complaint initially filed before it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (26821)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Investigation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26821&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission may, for the purpose of conducting any investigation`
  line `pertaining to the inquiry, utilise the services of any officer or investigation agency of the Central`
  line `Government or any State Government with the concurrence of the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of investigating into any matter pertaining to the inquiry, any officer or agency`
  line `whose services are utilised under sub-section (1) may, subject to the direction and control of the`
  line Commission,—
  line
  line `(a) summon and enforce the attendance of any person and examine him;`
  line
  line `(b) require the discovery and production of any document; and`
  line
  line `(c) requisition any public record or copy thereof from any office.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of section 15 shall apply in relation to any statement made by a person before any`
  line `officer or agency whose services are utilised under sub-section (1) as they apply in relation to any`
  line `statement made by a person in the course of giving evidence before the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer or agency whose services are utilised under sub-section (1) shall investigate into any`
  line `matter pertaining to the inquiry and submit a report thereon to the Commission within such period as`
  line `may be specified by the Commission in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commission shall satisfy itself about the correctness of the facts stated and the conclusion, if`
  line `any, arrived at in the report submitted to it under sub-section (4) and for this purpose the`
  line `Commission may make such inquiry (including the examination of the person or persons who`
  line `conducted or assisted in the investigation) as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (26822)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Statement made by persons to the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26822&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No statement made by a person in the`
  line `course of giving evidence before the Commission shall subject him to, or be used against him in, any`
  line `civil or criminal proceeding except a prosecution for giving false evidence by such statement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the statement—`
  line
  line `(a) is made in reply to the question which he is required by the Commission to answer; or`
  line
  line `(b) is relevant to the subject matter of the inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (26823)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Persons likely to be prejudicially affected to be heard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26823&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If, at any stage of the inquiry, the`
  line Commission—
  line
  line `(a) considers it necessary to inquire into the conduct of any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) is of the opinion that the reputation of any person is likely to be prejudicially affected by the`
  line inquiry,
  line
  line `it shall give to that person a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the inquiry and to produce evidence`
  line `in his defence:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply where the credit of a witness is being impeached.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (26824)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Inquiry into complaints.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26824&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Commission while inquiring into the complaints of violations of`
  line `human rights may—`
  line
  line `(i) call for information or report from the Central Government or any State Government or`
  line `any other authority or organisation subordinate thereto within such time as may be specified by it:`
  line
  line `Provided that—`
  line
  line `(a) if the information or report is not received within the time stipulated by the`
  line `Commission, it may proceed to inquire into the complaint on its own;`
  line
  line `(b) if, on receipt of information or report, the Commission is satisfied either that no`
  line `further inquiry is required or that the required action has been initiated or taken by the`
  line `concerned Government or authority, it may not proceed with the complaint and inform the`
  line `complainant accordingly;`
  line
  line `(ii) without prejudice to anything contained in clause (i), if it considers necessary, having regard`
  line `to the nature of the complaint, initiate an inquiry`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (26825)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Steps during and after inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 11, for section 18 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26825&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[18. Steps during and after inquiry.—The Commission may take any of the following steps during`
  line `or upon the completion of an inquiry held under this Act, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) where the inquiry discloses the commission of violation of human rights or negligence in the`
  line `prevention of violation of human rights or abetment thereof by a public servant, it may recommend to`
  line `the concerned Government or authority—`
  line
  line `(i) to make payment of compensation or damages to the complainant or to the victim or the`
  line `members of his family as the Commission may consider necessary;`
  line
  line `(ii) to initiate proceedings for prosecution or such other suitable action as the Commission`
  line `may deem fit against the concerned person or persons;`
  line
  line `(iii) to take such further action as it may think fit;`
  line
  line `(b) approach the Supreme Court or the High Court concerned for such directions, orders or writs`
  line `as that Court may deem necessary;`
  line
  line `(c) recommend to the concerned Government or authority at any stage of the inquiry for the grant`
  line `of such immediate interim relief to the victim or the members of his family as the Commission may`
  line `consider necessary;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of clause (e), provide a copy of the inquiry report to the petitioner or`
  line `his representative;`
  line
  line `(e) the Commission shall send a copy of its inquiry report together with its recommendations to`
  line `the concerned Government or authority and the concerned Government or authority shall, within a`
  line `period of one month, or such further time as the Commission may allow, forward its comments on the`
  line `report, including the action taken or proposed to be taken thereon, to the Commission;`
  line
  line `(f) the Commission shall publish its inquiry report together with the comments of the concerned`
  line `Government or authority, if any, and the action taken or proposed to be taken by the concerned`
  line `Government or authority on the recommendations of the Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (26826)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Procedure with respect to armed forces.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26826&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act, while dealing with complaints of violation of human rights by members of the armed forces,`
  line `the Commission shall adopt the following procedure, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) it may, either on its own motion or on receipt of a petition, seek a report from the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) after the receipt of the report, it may, either not proceed with the complaint or, as the case`
  line `may be, make its recommendations to that Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall inform the Commission of the action taken on the`
  line `recommendations within three months or such further time as the Commission may allow.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commission shall publish its report together with its recommendations made to the Central`
  line `Government and the action taken by that Government on such recommendations.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commission shall provide a copy of the report published under sub-section (3) to the`
  line `petitioner or his representative.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (26827)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Annual and special reports of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26827&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall submit an`
  line `annual report to the Central Government and to the State Government concerned and may at any time`
  line `submit special reports on any matter which, in its opinion, is of such urgency or importance that it`
  line `should not be deferred till submission of the annual report.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government and the State Government, as the case may be, shall cause the annual`
  line `and special reports of the Commission to be laid before each House of Parliament or the State Legislature`
  line `respectively, as the case may be, along with a memorandum of action taken or proposed to be taken on`
  line `the recommendations of the Commission and the reasons for non-acceptance of the recommendations, if`
  line any.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (26828)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Constitution of State Human Rights Commissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26828&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Government may constitute a`
  line `body to be known as the..................(name of the State) Human Rights Commission to exercise the`
  line `powers conferred upon, and to perform the functions assigned to, a State Commission under this`
  line Chapter.
  line
  line `^1[(2) The State Commission shall, with effect from such date as the State Government may by`
  line `notification specify, consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson who has been a ^2[Chief Justice or a Judge] of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) one Member who is, or has been, a Judge of a High Court or District Judge in the State with a`
  line `minimum of seven years experience as District Judge;`
  line
  line `(c) one Member to be appointed from among persons having knowledge of or practical`
  line `experience in matters relating to human rights.]`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be a Secretary who shall be the Chief Executive Officer of the State Commission and`
  line `^3[shall, subject to control of the Chairperson, exercise all administrative and financial powers of the State`
  line Commission].
  line
  line `(4) The headquarters of the State Commission shall be at such place as the State Government may,`
  line `by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(5) A State Commission may inquire into violation of human rights only in respect of matters`
  line `relatable to any of the entries enumerated in List II and List III in the Seventh Schedule to the`
  line `Constitution:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any such matter is already being inquired into by the Commission or any other`
  line `Commission duly constituted under any law for the time being in force, the State Commission shall`
  line `not inquire into the said matter:`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^5[(6) Two or more State Governments may, with the consent of a Chairperson or Member of a State`
  line `Commission, appoint such Chairperson or, as the case may be, such Member of another State`
  line `Commission simultaneously if such Chairperson or Member consents to such appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that every appointment made under this sub-section shall be made after obtaining the`
  line `recommendations of the Committee referred to in sub-section (1) of section 22 in respect of the State for`
  line `which a common Chairperson or Member, or both, as the case may be, is to be appointed.]`
  line
  line `^6[(7) Subject to the provisions of section 12, the Central Government may, by order, confer upon the`
  line `State Commission the functions relating to human rights being discharged by the Union territories, ^7[other`
  line `than Union territory of Delhi, Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh].`
  line
  line `(8) The functions relating to human rights in case of ^8[Union territory of Delhi, Union territory of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Union territory of Ladakh] shall be dealt with by the Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 12, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 5, for "Chief Justice" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 5, for "shall exercise such powers and discharge such functions of the State Commission as it may`
  line `delegate to him" (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The second proviso omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020,`
  line `vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 12 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O.`
  line `1123(E), for "other than Union territory of Delhi" dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation`
  line `(Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O.`
  line `1123(E), for "Union territory of Delhi" and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws)`
  line `Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (26829)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Appointment of Chairperson and other Members of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26829&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `22. Appointment of Chairperson and ^1`
  line `[Members] of State Commission.—(1) The Chairperson`
  line `and ^1`
  line `Members shall be appointed by the Governor by warrant under his hand and seal:`
  line
  line `Provided that every appointment under this sub-section shall be made after obtaining the`
  line `recommendation of a Committee consisting of—`
  line
  line `(a) the Chief Minister —chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) Speaker of the Legislative Assembly —member;`
  line
  line `(c) Minister in-charge of the Department`
  line `of Home in that State`
  line —member;
  line
  line `(d) Leader of the Opposition in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly`
  line `—member:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where there is a Legislative Council in a State, the Chairman of that Council and`
  line `the Leader of the Opposition in that Council shall also be members of the Committee:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no sitting Judge of a High Court or a sitting district judge shall be appointed except`
  line `after consultation with the Chief Justice of the High Court of the concerned State.`
  line
  line `(2) No appointment of a Chairperson or a Member of the State Commission shall be invalid merely`
  line `by reason of ^2`
  line `[any vacancy of any Member in the Committee referred to in sub-section (1)].`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "other Members" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "any vacancy in the Committee" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (26830)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Resignation and Removal of a Chairperson or a Member of the State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26830&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[23. Resignation and Removal of Chairperson or a Member of the State Commission].— ^2`
  line `(1)`
  line `The Chairperson or a Member of a State Commission may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed`
  line `to the Governor, resign his office.`
  line
  line `(1A) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the Chairperson or any Member of the State`
  line `Commission shall only be removed from his office by order of the President on the ground of proved`
  line `misbehaviour or incapacity after the Supreme Court, on a reference being made to it by the President, has,`
  line `on inquiry held in accordance with the procedure prescribed in that behalf by the Supreme Court, reported`
  line `that the Chairperson or such Member, as the case may be, ought on any such ground to be removed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything in ^3`
  line `[sub-section (1A)] the President may by order remove from office`
  line `the Chairperson or any ^4`
  line `[Member] if the Chairperson or such ^4[Member], as the case may be,`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) engages during his term of office in any paid employment outside the duties of his office; or`
  line
  line `(c) is unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of mind or body; or`
  line
  line `(d) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court;`
  line
  line `(e) is convicted and sentenced to imprisonment for an offence which in the opinion of the`
  line `President involves moral turpitude.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "Removal of a Member of the State Commission" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "sub-section" (1) (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 14, ibid., for "other Member" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (26831)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members of the State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26831&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[24. Term of office of Chairperson and Members of the State Commission.---(1) A person`
  line `appointed as Chairperson shall hold office for a term of ^2[three years] from the date on which he enters`
  line `upon his office or until he attains the age of seventy years, whichever is earlier ^3[and shall be eligible for`
  line re-appointment].
  line
  line `(2) A person appointed as a Member shall hold office for a term of ^2[three years] from the date on`
  line `which he enters upon his office and shall be eligible for re-appointment ^4***:`
  line
  line `Provided that no Member shall hold office after he has attained the age of seventy years.`
  line
  line `(3) On ceasing to hold office, a Chairperson or a Member shall be ineligible for further employment`
  line `under the Government of a State or under the Government of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 15, for section 24 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 2019, s. 6, for “five years” (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
  line
  line `4. The words “for another term of five years” omitted by Act 19 of 2019, s. 6 (w.e.f. 2-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (26832)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Member to act as Chairperson or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26832&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson by reason of his death,`
  line `resignation or otherwise, the Governor may, by notification, authorise one of the Members to act as the`
  line `Chairperson until the appointment of a new Chairperson to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairperson is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence on leave or`
  line `otherwise, such one of the Members as the Governor may, by notification, authorise in this behalf, shall`
  line `discharge the functions of the Chairperson until the date on which the Chairperson resumes his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (26833)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s.16, ibid., for section 26 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26833&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[26. Terms and conditions of service of Chairperson and Members of State Commission.— The`
  line `salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service of, the Chairperson and`
  line `Members shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson or a Member shall be varied to his disadvantage after his appointment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (26834)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Officers and other staff of the State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26834&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall make`
  line `available to the Commission—`
  line
  line `(a) an officer not below the rank of a Secretary to the State Government who shall be the`
  line `Secretary of the State Commission; and`
  line
  line `(b) such police and investigative staff under an officer not below the rank of an Inspector`
  line `General of Police and such other officers and staff as may be necessary for the efficient`
  line `performance of the functions of the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as may be made by the State Government in this behalf, the State`
  line `Commission may appoint such other administrative, technical and scientific staff as it may consider`
  line necessary.
  line
  line `(3) The salaries, allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other staff appointed under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (26835)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Annual and special reports of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26835&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall submit an`
  line `annual report to the State Government and may at any time submit special reports on any matter which,`
  line `in its opinion, is of such urgency or importance that it should not be deferred till submission of the`
  line `annual report.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall cause the annual and special reports of the State Commission to`
  line `be laid before each House of State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such Legislature`
  line `consists of one House, before that House along with a memorandum of action taken or proposed to be`
  line `taken on the recommendations of the State Commission and the reasons for non-acceptance of the`
  line `recommendations, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (26836)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Application of certain provisions relating to National Human Rights Commission to State Commissions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26836&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of sections 9, 10, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17 and 18 shall apply to a State`
  line `Commission and shall have effect, subject to the following modifications, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) references to "Commission" shall be construed as references to "State Commission";`
  line
  line `(b) in section 10, in sub-section (3), for the word "Secretary-General", the word`
  line `"Secretary" shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(c) in section 12, clause (f) shall be omitted;`
  line
  line `(d) in section 17, in clause (i), the words "Central Government or any" shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (26837)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Human Rights Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26837&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of providing speedy trial of offences arising out of`
  line `violation of human rights, the State Government may, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the`
  line `High Court, by notification, specify for each district a Court of Session to be a Human Rights Court to`
  line `try the said offences:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply if—`
  line
  line `(a) a Court of Session is already specified as a special court; or`
  line
  line `(b) a special court is already constituted,`
  line
  line `for such offences under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (26838)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Special Public Prosecutor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26838&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `For every Human Rights Court, the State Government shall, by`
  line `notification, specify a Public Prosecutor or appoint an advocate who has been in practice as an advocate`
  line `for not less than seven years, as a Special Public Prosecutor for the purpose of conducting cases in`
  line `that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (26839)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Grants by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26839&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, after due`
  line `appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission by way of grants such`
  line `sums of money as the Central Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing the functions under this`
  line `Act, and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (26840)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Grants by the State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26840&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, after due, appropriation`
  line `made by Legislature by law in this behalf, pay to the State Commission by way of grants such sums`
  line `of money as the State Government may think fit for being utilised for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Commission may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing the functions under`
  line `Chapter V, and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the grants referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (26841)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26841&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant`
  line `records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges and the`
  line `authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has in connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Commission, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the Central Government by the Commission and the Central Government shall`
  line `cause the audit report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (26842)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Accounts and audit of State Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26842&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Commission shall maintain`
  line `proper accounts and other relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed by the State Government in consultation with the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the State Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General`
  line `at such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such`
  line `audit shall be payable by the State Commission to the Comptroller and Auditor-General.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General and any person appointed by him in connection with the`
  line `audit of the accounts of the State Commission under this Act shall have the same rights and privileges`
  line `and the authority in connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General generally has`
  line `in connection with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the State Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the State Commission, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be`
  line `forwarded annually to the State Government by the State Commission and the State Government shall`
  line `cause the audit report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is received, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (26843)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Matters not subject to jurisdiction of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26843&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall not`
  line `inquire into any matter which is pending before a State Commission or any other Commission duly`
  line `constituted under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission or the State Commission shall not inquire into any matter after the expiry of`
  line `one year from the date on which the act constituting violation of human rights is alleged to have been`
  line committed.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (26844)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Constitution of special investigation teams.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26844&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other`
  line `law for the time being in force, where the Government considers it necessary so to do, it may constitute`
  line `one or more special investigation teams, consisting of such police officers as it thinks necessary for`
  line `purposes of investigation and prosecution of offences arising out of violations of human rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (26845)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26845&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the Central Government, State Government, Commission, the State Commission or any Member thereof`
  line `or any person acting under the direction either of the Central Government, State Government,`
  line `Commission or the State Commission in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to`
  line `be done in pursuance of this Act or of any rules or any order made thereunder or in respect of the`
  line `publication by or under the authority of the Central Government, State Government, Commission or`
  line `the State Commission of any report, paper or proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (26846)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Members and officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26846&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Every Member of the Commission, State`
  line `Commission and every officer appointed or authorised by the Commission or the State Commission`
  line `to exercise functions under this Act shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (26847)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 2006, s.17, for "Members" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26847&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the ^1`
  line [Chairperson
  line `and Members] under section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which other administrative, technical and scientific staff may be`
  line `appointed by the Commission and the salaries and allowances of officers and other staff under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) any other power of a civil court required to be prescribed under clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which the annual statement of accounts is to be prepared by the Commission`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 34; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_a:
  sectionId (26848)
  sectionNo 40A
  orderNo 41
  title `Power to make rules retrospectively.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 2000, s. 2 (w.e.f. 11-12-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26848&sectionno=40A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_40_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[40A. Power to make rules retrospectively.—The power to make rules under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 40 shall include the power to make such rules or any of them retrospectively`
  line `from a date not earlier than the date on which this Act received the assent of the President, but no such`
  line `retrospective effect shall be given to any such rule so as to prejudicially affect the interests of any person`
  line `to whom such rule may be applicable.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40_b:
  sectionId (26849)
  sectionNo 40B
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of Commission to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 43 of 2006, s. 18 (w.e.f. 23-11-2006).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26849&sectionno=40B&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_40_b_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[40B. Power of Commission to make regulations.—(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and`
  line `the rules made thereunder, the Commission may, with the previous approval of the Central Government,`
  line `by notification, make regulations to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed by the Commission under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the returns and statistics to be furnished by the State Commissions;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter which has to be, or may be, specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made by the Commission under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (26850)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. Act 43 of 2006, s. 19, for "the Members" (w.e.f. 23-11-2006)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26850&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of ^1`
  line [the
  line `Chairperson and Members] under section 26;`
  line
  line `(b) the conditions subject to which other administrative, technical and scientific staff may be`
  line `appointed by the State Commission and the salaries and allowances of officers and other staff`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(c) the form in which the annual statement of accounts is to be prepared under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 35.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of the State Legislature where it consists of two Houses, or where such`
  line `Legislature consists of one House, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (26851)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26851&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of the period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (26852)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704&sectionId=26852&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_24_000010_199410_1517807322704
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Protection of Human Rights Ordinance, 1993 (Ord. 30 of 1993) is`
  line `hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance,`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
